main event: A civilian observer spotted an unidentified flying object near the Ley Ranch Airport in Denver, Colorado on October 31, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 2 hours.
There were multiple witness accounts of the sighting.
The Air Force's Aerial Phenomena Office received an unsolicited report of the sighting.
The Air Force requested information from local airports and aerial advertisers to determine if any aircraft or balloons were in the area at the time.
The Denver Department of Public Works reported that no unidentified lights or aerial phenomena were reported to their office on the night of October 31st.
